Description: Solid-cast fitting for a figure in copper alloy; representing a was-sceptre; no detail visible; lower and upper parts broken off; corroded; two fragments glued together.
Curator's comments: Published in Andrews 1994, 75. See other examples in: Petrie 1914, pl. IV no. 54. Andrews, C. 1994, Amulets of Ancient Egypt, London. Petrie, W.M.F. 1914, Amulets, London.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (MB.253) (phase 3)
